    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "c21c4a85_86d24fe1",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 360,
      "author": {
        "id": 8223
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-04T01:23:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m confused what the *rowsDecoded semantics should be in case of kIncomplete. I thought *rowsDecoded was set to what we completely decoded, and with kIncomplete, we haven\u0027t completely decoded those rows. But if you think it matches the semantics better here, I\u0027ll go with it.",
      "parentUuid": "61615f4a_44cc74d0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 358,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 360,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5a0a6738_e214d916",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 360,
      "author": {
        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-05T20:12:59Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "\u003e I thought *rowsDecoded was set to what we completely decoded, and with kIncomplete, we\n\u003e haven\u0027t completely decoded those rows.\n\nNo, it\u0027s intended to be the rows that have been initialized. (The comment actually says this, but the name is misleading.) The point is that client (or SkSampledCodec) can then initialize the remaining rows.\n\nA potentially interesting thing to return is something like \"how much of the image was decoded?\". We could have initialized everything to transparent but not really decoded anything, in which case the client may not want to display the result. But we don\u0027t currently have a good way to return that.",
      "parentUuid": "c21c4a85_86d24fe1",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 358,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 360,
        "endChar": 5
      },
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5e62cad0_e58218b5",
        "filename": "src/codec/SkWuffsCodec.cpp",
