        "id": 5255
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-11-02T17:42:42Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It might make sense to set the error to result and continue. (Then I can move back the setting of rowsDecoded.) My idea of kErrorInInput is that we maybe decoded part of the image, but then it had an error that forced us to stop. So there might be something to draw here.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 369,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 370,
        "endChar": 38
      },
      "revId": "8a250dc152e4a93801f77cbcb19c2e490656b67b",
